# ============================================================================
# SECRET HYGIENE — these patterns guarantee no key/secret can ever be committed.
# .env holds the three T3N private keys; it must NEVER ship.
# ============================================================================

# --- Secrets: env files (root + any nested) ---
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
!.env.example

# --- Convenience symlink (points into ignored node_modules; not a deliverable) ---
on-the-record/node_modules

# --- Build / dependency dirs (never ship) ---
# Rust build output (target/) is excluded everywhere: it is large, reproducible
# via `cargo build`, and the only deliverable inside it (the contract wasm) is
# committed at a stable path alongside the source instead — see note below.
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
target/
**/target/

# --- Rehearsal scratch (not part of the entry) ---
_rehearsal/

# ============================================================================
# terminal3-agent-mesh/ is an OLDER beta tree that is NOT part of this entry.
# It contains a real throwaway secp256k1 private key (recon-findings.json) and
# demo "sk_live_*" tokens (src/*.ts). Ignore the whole tree, then RE-INCLUDE
# only the shippable contract source: contracts/on-the-record/ and everything
# under it (target/ is still excluded by the **/target/ rule above, so the
# build tree does not ship; the deliverable wasm is committed at the stable
# sibling path noted below).
#
# To re-include a path whose parent is ignored, every parent directory must be
# un-ignored too, and the leaf needs a recursive /** so its contents follow.
# ============================================================================
terminal3-agent-mesh/*
!terminal3-agent-mesh/contracts/
terminal3-agent-mesh/contracts/*
!terminal3-agent-mesh/contracts/on-the-record/
!terminal3-agent-mesh/contracts/on-the-record/**

# Note: there is NO "*.wasm" ignore rule on purpose — the compiled contract
# artifact is a deliverable and ships. The committed copy lives at the stable
# path terminal3-agent-mesh/contracts/on-the-record/on_the_record.wasm (a
# sibling of the source), which is NOT inside any ignored target/ build dir, so
# it is reliably tracked. The build-tree copy under target/ stays ignored.
